      • Department

        public Department(java.lang.String address,
                  java.lang.String name,
                  java.lang.String internalCode,
                  Collaborator responsibleCollaborator)

        Department

        Description: Constructs a new Department object with the specified address, name, internal code, and responsible collaborator.

        Preconditions:

        • The address, name, and internalCode parameters must be of type String.
        • The responsibleCollaborator parameter must be an instance of Collaborator.

        Postconditions:

        • A new Department object is created with the provided address, name, internal code, and responsible collaborator.
        • The Department object is also initialized with an empty ArrayList of Requests.
        Parameters:
        address - The address of the department.
        name - The name of the department.
        internalCode - The internal code of the department.
        responsibleCollaborator - The collaborator responsible for the department.

    • Method Detail

      • registerRequest

        public java.lang.String registerRequest(java.lang.String subject,
                                        java.lang.String description,
                                        Collaborator responsibleCollaborator)

        registerRequest

        Description: Registers a new request within the department with the specified subject, description, and responsible collaborator.

        Preconditions:

        • subject must be a valid string representing the subject of the request.
        • description must be a valid string representing the description of the request.
        • responsibleCollaborator must be a valid instance of Collaborator representing the responsible collaborator.

        Postconditions:

        • A new request is registered within the department with the specified subject, description, and responsible collaborator.
        • The newly created request is added to the list of requests associated with the department. The department itself is also saved withing the request.
        • A message indicating the success of the request registration is returned.
        Parameters:
        subject - The subject of the request.
        description - The description of the request.
        responsibleCollaborator - The responsible collaborator for the request.
        Returns:
        A message indicating the success of the request registration.

      • changeRequestStatus

        public java.lang.String[] changeRequestStatus(int intSubject,
                                              int intStatusType)

        changeRequestStatus

        Description: Changes the status of a pending request within the department based on user input. This method retrieves the pending request from the department's list of pending requests by index (getPendingRequests()) and sets its status based on the provided status type (Request.setStatus(StatusType)). If the status type indicates approval or denial, the method also sets the classification date for the request. If the request is set to pending, it will only return a message indicating that the status has been left untouched. Finally, the methods returns in a String Array the internalCode of the department (getInternalCode()), the subject of the request (Request.getSubject()) and the result of the operation.

        Preconditions:

        • intSubject and intStatusType must be valid integers.
        • The department must have pending requests in its list of pending requests.
        • The request index (intSubject) must be within the range of pending requests.
        • The status type index (intStatusType) must be a number between 1 and 3.

        Postconditions:

        • The status of the selected pending request within the department is changed based on the provided status type.
        • If the status type indicates approval or denial, the classification date for the request is set to the current date and time.
        • If the status type is left as pending, it will only return a message.
        • A message indicating the result of the status change is returned.
        Parameters:
        intSubject - The index of the pending request within the department's list of pending requests.
        intStatusType - The index representing the new status type for the request.
        Returns:
        An array containing the department's internal code, the subject of the request, and a message indicating the result of the status change.

      • isDuplicateRequest

        public boolean isDuplicateRequest(java.lang.String subject)

        isDuplicateRequest

        Description: Checks if there is a duplicate request with the specified subject within the department. Uses the method searchRequest(String) in order to check if there is a duplicate or not.

        Preconditions:

        • subject must be a valid string representing the subject of the request.

        Postconditions:

        • Returns true if there is a duplicate request with the specified subject within the department; otherwise, returns false.
        Parameters:
        subject - The subject of the request to check for duplication.
        Returns:
        true if there is a duplicate request with the specified subject within the department; otherwise, false.

      • searchRequest

        public Request searchRequest(java.lang.String subject)

        searchRequest

        Description: Searches for a request with the specified subject within the department.

        Preconditions:

        • subject must be a valid string representing the subject of the request.

        Postconditions:

        • If a request with the provided subject is found within the department, the request object is returned; otherwise, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        subject - The subject of the request to search for.
        Returns:
        The request object with the specified subject, if found; otherwise, null.

      • oneMinPendingRequest

        public boolean oneMinPendingRequest()

        oneMinPendingRequest

        Description: Checks if there is at least one pending request in the department awaiting approval. This method iterates through the list of requests in the department and checks if any request has a status indicating that it is pending approval.

        Preconditions:

        • The requests list must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • The method returns true if there is at least one pending request in the department awaiting approval (status type 1), otherwise it returns false.
        Returns:
        true if there is at least one pending request in the department awaiting approval, false otherwise.

      • getPendingRequests

        public java.util.ArrayList<Request> getPendingRequests()

        getPendingRequests

        Description: Retrieves a list of pending requests awaiting approval in the department. This method iterates through the list of requests in the department and adds those with a status indicating that they are pending approval to the list of pending requests.

        Preconditions:

        • The requests list must be initialized.

        Postconditions:

        • A list of pending requests awaiting approval in the department is retrieved.
        • The list contains requests with a status indicating that they are pending approval (status type 1 with StatusType.intToStatus(int)).
        Returns:
        A list of pending requests awaiting approval in the department.

      • displayStatusTypes

        public static java.lang.String displayStatusTypes()

        displayStatusTypes

        Description: Retrieves a message displaying the available status types for requests. This method delegates the task of generating the message to the Request.displayStatusTypes() method in the Request class.

        Preconditions:

        • The Request class must implement the Request.displayStatusTypes() method to provide a message with available status types.

        Postconditions:

        • A message containing the available status types for requests is retrieved and returned.
        Returns:
        A message containing the available status types for requests.
